African National Congress (ANC) Secretary General Ace Magashule has offered his condolences to the families of five people who were killed in a bus crash on R66 between Melmoth and eShowe in northern KwaZulu-Natal on Saturday. Magashule addressed members of the 12 Apostles Church at Mevamhlophe in eMpangeni on Sunday. The victims were on route from Johannesburg to the church’s 40th anniversary celebrations in the area when their bus overturned. Among those killed was an 11-month-old baby.  Earlier, Magashule and two KwaZulu-Natal MEC’s visited the scene of the crash. The names of the deceased have not yet been disclosed. Click below for more on the story: 